RENDER STUFF DOCUMENTATION:
	to draw triangles you need a shader
	blah blah blah blah blah blah blah blah blah blah
	that passed the point in triangle and depth tests
	and recieves a pointer to Struct pixeldata-
	must return an Int
	--struct pixeldata ---
	Vec3D center -> the screen position of pixel with z coordinate
	Vec3D localpos -> the (barycentric) local position of a point in a triangle
	int tri_index -> the index of the triangle for which the pixel renders
	int x -> the x coordinate of the point's left top corner(for array indexing)
	int y -> the y coordinate of the point's left top corner(for array indexing)
	void * userarg -> a pointer to user data used by the shader(can be null if the shader doesn't want it)
	
	WHAT YOU NEED TO RENDER

	a shader given the struct returns int color

	a buffer - created wia createBuffer(width, height); with buffer widths in pixels
	IT CONTAINS BOTH PIXEL AND DEPTH BUFFER
	
	your TRIANGLE DATA in form of an Vec3D array where size %3 = 0;
